node.label: createQQPlot
node.description: There are several ways to asses the normality hypothesis in a data set visual inspection through plots is an useful method These are graphical techniques for assessing whether or not a data set is approximately normally distributed The data are plotted against a theoretical normal distribution in such a way that the points should form an approximate straight line QQ quantilequantile zscores vs Expected zscores

node.label: createRGPlot

node.label: MicroarrayDataDoubleScanMoby
node.description: The devices used for measuring intensities are neither perfect nor unlimited Saturation and quantization appear when scanning and can barely be removed This service implements a proprietary technique for improving the quality of scanned data Garcia de la Nava et al

node.label: MicroArrayDataLowess
node.description: This procedure adjust the data to a lowess curve Since data are a cloud of points the adjust will never be perfect Lowess performs a robust adjust closer points are considered and outliers are discarded This is quite adequate for those experiment data in which only a small number of data shows different values which is the case of most gene expression data in which we expect only a minor number of genes are expected to have differential expression In this way the curve adjust to zero those genes with similar expression values Lowess procedure needs three parameters F Parameter Is the fraction of relevant points As was previously mentioned lowess adjust assign a greater weight to close points as a function of the pairwise distance This parameter set the number of points to be considered as close For high values of F the curve is smoother Usually this value is set in the range NSteps parameter Number of algorithm iterations In each step the curve is better adjusted and smoother As the algorithm proceed it will trend towards the closer points Usually this value is set in the range Delta parameter When the number of steps is high ie greater than this parameter speedup calculations Otherwise it should be zero
